.TH LHSSH 1 "March 2026" "lhssh 2.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
lhssh \- local host SSH scanner and connection manager
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lhssh
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.br
.B lhssh
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] \fITARGET\fR [\fICOMMAND\fR...]
.br
.B lhssh
.B \-6
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.br
.B lhssh
.B \-h
|
.B \-V
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B lhssh
is a dependency-free bash utility for scanning local networks for SSH-enabled hosts and managing connections.
It supports IPv4 range scanning, IPv6 link-local discovery via multicast ping, and direct SSH connections using short notation.
.PP
.B lhssh
operates in two modes:
.TP
.B Scan mode (default)
Discovers SSH hosts on the local network.
IPv4 mode iterates an IP range and probes with
.BR ssh-keyscan (1)
or
.BR nc (1).
IPv6 mode sends an ICMPv6 all-nodes multicast ping and filters responders through
.BR ssh-keyscan (1).
.TP
.B Connect mode
Establishes an SSH connection to a specified target.
TARGET can be a short octet (e.g., \fB152\fR expands to \fB192.168.1.152\fR),
a full IPv4 address, or an IPv6 address with optional zone ID
(e.g., \fBfe80::1%enp12s0\fR).
If COMMAND is given, it is executed on the remote host with timeout protection;
otherwise an interactive session is opened.
.PP
The companion script
.B lhssh\-cmd
wraps
.B lhssh
to execute commands across all discovered hosts, with optional parallel execution.
.SH OPTIONS
.SS General Options
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show help message and exit.
.TP
.BR \-V ", " \-\-version
Show version information and exit.
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-verbose
Enable verbose output. Use \fB\-vv\fR for debug output.
.TP
.BR \-q ", " \-\-quiet
Suppress all non-essential output.
.SS Display Options
.TP
.BR \-s ", " \-\-short
Show IP addresses only (no header or hostnames).
.TP
.BR \-p ", " \-\-supershort
Show only the last octet of IPv4 addresses. For IPv6, outputs the full address.
.TP
.BR \-H ", " \-\-with\-hostname
Add hostname to \fB\-s\fR/\fB\-p\fR output as a tab-separated second column.
.TP
.BR \-C ", " \-\-no\-color
Disable colored output.
.SS Network Options
.TP
.BR \-n ", " \-\-network " \fIPREFIX\fR"
Set the network prefix for IPv4 scanning (default: \fB192.168.1.\fR).
Supports CIDR /24 notation (e.g., \fB10.99.10.0/24\fR), which sets the prefix and
scans the full 1\-254 range.
.TP
.BR \-b ", " \-\-begin " \fIIP\fR"
Start IP for scanning, last octet (default: \fB50\fR).
.TP
.BR \-f ", " \-\-finish " \fIIP\fR"
End IP for scanning, last octet (default: \fB230\fR).
.TP
.BR \-6 ", " \-\-ipv6
Scan IPv6 link-local neighbors instead of IPv4.
Uses multicast ping (\fBff02::1\fR) for discovery.
.TP
.BR \-I ", " \-\-interface " \fIIFACE\fR"
Network interface for IPv6 scanning (default: auto-detected from default route).
Implies \fB\-6\fR.
.SS SSH Options
.TP
.BR \-u ", " \-\-user " \fIUSERNAME\fR"
SSH username (default: current user).
.TP
.BR \-t ", " \-\-timeout " \fISECS\fR"
Connection timeout in seconds (default: \fB10\fR).
In IPv6 scan mode, also controls the multicast ping timeout (converted to milliseconds).
.TP
.BR \-T ", " \-\-session\-time " \fISECS\fR"
Session timeout for remote command execution (default: \fB600\fR).
Does not apply to interactive sessions.
.SS Host Blocking Options
These options use
.BR nft (8)
to temporarily block hosts at the firewall level.
Rules are stored in a dedicated nft table (\fBinet lhssh\fR) and are
cleared on reboot. Requires sudo privileges.
.TP
.BR \-K ", " \-\-kill " \fIIP\fR"
Block an IP address. Requires a full IPv4 or IPv6 address (not short octets).
.TP
.BR \-U ", " \-\-unkill " \fIIP\fR"
Unblock a previously blocked IP address.
.TP
.BR \-L ", " \-\-list\-killed
Show all currently blocked IP addresses.
.SS Configuration Options
.TP
.BR \-l ", " \-\-list
Show current configuration.
.TP
.BR \-e ", " \-\-edit
Open configuration file in \fB$EDITOR\fR (default: \fBnano\fR).
.TP
.BR \-S ", " \-\-save\-config
Save current options to configuration file.
.SH EXAMPLES
Scan the default network for SSH hosts:
.RS
.nf
.B lhssh
.fi
.RE
.PP
Connect to host .152 using short notation:
.RS
.nf
.B lhssh 152
.fi
.RE
.PP
Run a command on a remote host:
.RS
.nf
.B lhssh 152 uptime
.fi
.RE
.PP
Scan a different network range:
.RS
.nf
.B lhssh \-n 10.0.0. \-b 1 \-f 50
.fi
.RE
.PP
Scan a /24 network using CIDR notation:
.RS
.nf
.B lhssh \-n 10.99.10.0/24
.fi
.RE
.PP
Scan IPv6 link-local neighbors:
.RS
.nf
.B lhssh \-6
.fi
.RE
.PP
Scan IPv6 on a specific interface:
.RS
.nf
.B lhssh \-6 \-I enp12s0
.fi
.RE
.PP
Connect to an IPv6 host:
.RS
.nf
.B lhssh fe80::1%enp12s0 hostname
.fi
.RE
.PP
List IPs with hostnames (tab-separated, for scripting):
.RS
.nf
.B lhssh \-sH
.fi
.RE
.PP
Execute a command on all discovered hosts:
.RS
.nf
for ip in $(lhssh \-p); do
    lhssh $ip "hostname \-f"
done
.fi
.RE
.PP
Block a rogue device (temporary \(em cleared on reboot):
.RS
.nf
.B lhssh \-K 192.168.1.99
.fi
.RE
.PP
List currently blocked hosts:
.RS
.nf
.B lhssh \-L
.fi
.RE
.PP
Unblock a host:
.RS
.nf
.B lhssh \-U 192.168.1.99
.fi
.RE
.PP
Run a command on all hosts in parallel using lhssh\-cmd:
.RS
.nf
.B lhssh\-cmd \-p "df \-h"
.fi
.RE
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
General error.
.TP
.B 22
Invalid argument (bad option, invalid IP octet, invalid IPv6 address).
.TP
.B 24
Operation timed out.
.TP
.B 25
Host unreachable.
.TP
.B 130
Interrupted by Ctrl+C.
.TP
.B 255
SSH connection failed.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/lhssh/lhssh.conf
System-wide default configuration. Loaded first; user config overrides.
.TP
.I ~/.lhssh.conf
Legacy user configuration (searched first).
.TP
.I ~/.config/lhssh/lhssh.conf
XDG-compliant user configuration. Auto-created on first run if no config exists.
.TP
.I /etc/bash_completion.d/lhssh
Bash completion for lhssh and lhssh\-cmd.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B NO_COLOR
If set, disables colored output. See \fIhttps://no\-color.org\fR.
.TP
.B EDITOR
Editor used by \fB\-e\fR to edit the configuration file.
.TP
.B USER
Default SSH username when \fB\-u\fR is not specified.
.TP
.B XDG_CONFIG_HOME
Base directory for user configuration (default: \fI~/.config\fR).
.SH SECURITY
.IP \(bu 2
Key-based authentication only (\fBPasswordAuthentication=no\fR).
.IP \(bu 2
SSH host key checking set to \fBaccept\-new\fR (auto-accepts new host keys, rejects changed keys).
.IP \(bu 2
Configuration files created with mode 600.
.IP \(bu 2
IPv6 address input validated against injection characters.
